      <abstract>
        <p>The Pechmann reaction of substituted phenols <bold>1a-e</bold> with methyl acetoacetate (<bold>2</bold>) can be activated by boron trifluoride dihydrate (<bold>3</bold>) to give the corresponding 4-methylcoumarin derivatives <bold>4a-e</bold> in excellent yield (98-99 %).</p>
      </abstract>
